RT  Escherichia coli serogroup O2 and O28ac O-antigen gene cluster
RT  sequences and detection of pathogenic E. coli O2 and O28ac by PCR.
RA  Fratamico PM, Yan X, Liu Y, DebRoy C, Byrne B, Monaghan A, Fanning S,
RA  Bolton D;
RL  Can J Microbiol. 2010;56:308-316.
CC  The O2 antigen is a branched pentasaccharide observed in strains 1.2741
CC  and 9.1649. It consists of the repeating unit
CC  [->3)a-L-Rha-((2<-1)-a-D-Fuc3NAc)-(1->2)-a-L-Rha-(1->3)-b-L-Rha-(1->4)-
CC  b-D-GlcNAc-(1->]. Genes for the biosynthesis of Rhamnose and
CC  3-acylamino-fucose (Fuc3NAc), both of which arise from the same
CC  intermediate, 4,6-dideoxy-4-oxo-dTDP-D-glucose, are found within the
CC  cluster.
**  Identical to (?) cross-reacts with O74
